[4] Switzerland (Geneva Canton)
Date: Tue 24 May 2022
Source: Government of Switzerland Department of Security, Population and Health (DSPS) press release [in French, trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.ge.ch/document/variole-du-singe-premier-cas-detecte-dans-canton-geneve


Today [24 May 2022], a 1st case of monkeypox has been confirmed in the canton of Geneva. This is the 2nd confirmed case in Switzerland, the 1st case having been confirmed on 21 May 2022 in the canton of Bern.

In accordance with the recommendations of the FOPH [Federal Office of Public Health], the person concerned is in good general condition, not currently requiring hospitalization but in isolation, until the complete resolution of the disease. Preliminary evidence indicates that she was infected during a trip abroad. An epidemiological investigation is underway to warn people who could be exposed.

